==Open Social Web Standards==

#[[Open ID]] [http://openid.net/] - distributed authentication and basic profiles 
#[http://oauth.net/ oAuth] - distributed (delegated) authorization 
#[http://portablecontacts.net/ Portable Contacts] - making your contact list portable and interoperable 
#[http://activitystrea.ms/ ActivityStrea.ms] - semantic structure for activity streams so distributed streams can be meaningfully merged and split 
#PubSubHubbub or (PuSH) - distributed realtime publishing 
#[http://www.salmon-protocol.org/ Salmon] - ensuring that a distributed comment thread stays connected to the source (uses PuSH) 
#[http://code.google.com/p/webfinger/ Webfinger] - enable profile lookups from an email address

==Combined Standards==

#OpenID Connect - combines OpenID and oAuth 
#OStatus - combines ActivityStreams, PuSH, Salmon, Webfinger 



==Implementation in Major Networks==

#Google Buzz: ActivityStreams, OAuth, PubSubHubbub, Salmon, WebFinger, OpenID 
#Myspace: ActivityStreams, OpenID, OAuth, OpenSocial, PuSH (coming soon) 
#Twitter: oAuth 
#Facebook: oAuth, OpenID (consumer), ActivityStreams 


